"""Intent 04 recommendation_products_by_images — 5-node LangGraph image recommendation.

S-09 V-SLICE Phiên Sx09-C per D-S09-NN-A LAW + D-S09-NN-B LAW + D-S09-NN-C LAW
(cornerstone) + 5 mid-task amendments C-S09-O/P/Q/R/S.

Customer chụp ảnh sản phẩm → ICP trả 10 sản phẩm gợi ý kèm reason per item
trong ~3 giây. Cross-modal CLIP-multilingual shared space pathway (image_description
→ embed → image_embedding) eliminates separate image encoder per D-S09-NN-C LAW.

Graph topology (5 nodes sequential per Pattern A reuse + S-04 D-S04-13 LAW):

    START
      ├─► vision_analyze       (Node 1)
      │       └─► MCP vision.analyze (Gemini 2.5 Flash multimodal)
      │           emit phase_progress {phase_id:1, label:"Đọc nội dung sản phẩm",
      │                                meta:"Gemini Vision", status:"active"}
      │           3-threshold blur check Ω₂ per C-S07-J reuse
      │           → on blur/error: emit error E_VISION_BLUR → END
      ├─► build_query_desc     (Node 2)
      │       └─► template f"{category} {attrs} {ocr_text} brand:... flavor:..."
      ├─► parallel_fetch       (Node 3 — asyncio.gather)
      │       ├─► MCP vespa.image_nearest_neighbor (top 30 visual_sim + trend)
      │       ├─► MCP analytics.co_purchased (top 20 collab freq per category)
      │       └─► MCP analytics.product_corpus_size (dynamic N per C-S09-Q)
      │           emit phase_progress {phase_id:2, label:"Tìm sản phẩm tương tự",
      │                                meta:f"Đang so khớp với {N} sản phẩm shop..."}
      ├─► blend_and_rank       (Node 4 — Python composite per D-S09-NN-A LAW)
      │       composite_per_hit = 0.5*visual_sim + 0.3*collab_norm + 0.2*trending
      │       attach sub_scores + match_type ∈ {visual, collab, trending}
      │       top 30 sort, take top 10 for response
      └─► attach_reasons       (Node 5 — parallel LLM Gemini 2.5 Flash)
              emit phase_progress {phase_id:3, label:"Xếp hạng + sinh lý do gợi ý"}
              asyncio.gather LLM calls 5s timeout (D-S04-15 LAW)
              emit product_ready PER product (D-S04-14 LAW progressive)
              emit products final canonical list + final event {detected, co_purchase_hint}
              await saver.adelete_thread(rid)  (Strategy β fast-path cleanup)
              → END

Phase mapping LOCKED per C-S09-P + Rule 6 LAW (mockup intent-04-state-A-loading.html):
    0 = upload    → "Tải ảnh lên"
    1 = vision    → "Đọc nội dung sản phẩm" + meta "Gemini Vision"
    2 = embed     → "Tìm sản phẩm tương tự" + DYNAMIC meta "Đang so khớp với {N} sản phẩm shop..."
    3 = rank      → "Xếp hạng + sinh lý do gợi ý"

NOTE: S-09 uses 0-indexed convention (S-04 canonical), NOT S-07 1-indexed.

Signal blend weights per D-S09-NN-A LAW (default visual since uploaded image):
    visual:   {v: 0.5, c: 0.3, t: 0.2}    (this graph default for BE composite)
    collab:   {v: 0.2, c: 0.7, t: 0.1}    (FE client-side re-rank when chip toggled)
    trending: {v: 0.2, c: 0.1, t: 0.7}

Reuses 100% from S-04/S-07 emit per session handoff §6.4:
    - state.IcpState — extended +4 S-09 transient fields per state.py B2 amendment
    - tools.llm_client.get_llm_client + LLMTimeout — 5s default per D-S04-15 LAW
    - tools.mcp_client.McpClient + McpError — JSON-RPC 2.0 client
    - tools.redis_publisher.RedisPublisher — publish_sse helper
    - prompts.load_prompt — for 3 NEW recommend_*.txt prompts
    - importing_by_images.py:97-134 is_vision_blur_error — 3-threshold Ω₂ reuse
    - importing_by_images.py:141-147 _current_trace_id — OTel trace helper reuse
    - searching_by_text.py:878-1020 compile_X_graph pattern + Strategy β cleanup

Reference:
    - slices/S-09_decisions-log.md D-S09-NN-A/B/C/D/E LAW + C-S09-A..S
    - slices/S-09_BRIEF.md Sections 3-6
    - docs/phases/PHASE_05_RECO_ANALYTICS.md §B/C (image embedding + co_purchased)
    - docs/mockups/intent-04/intent-04-state-A-loading.html lines 185-265
    - apps/ai/src/graphs/intents/searching_by_text.py (Pattern A reference)
    - apps/ai/src/graphs/intents/importing_by_images.py (image flow precedent)
"""

from __future__ import annotations

import asyncio
import json
import os
from typing import Any

import structlog
from langgraph.checkpoint.redis.aio import AsyncRedisSaver
from langgraph.graph import END, START, StateGraph
from langgraph.types import Command
from opentelemetry import trace

from ...state import IcpState
from ...tools.llm_client import LLMError, LLMTimeout, get_llm_client
from ...tools.mcp_client import McpClient, McpError
from ...tools.redis_publisher import RedisPublisher
from ...prompts import load_prompt

_tracer = trace.get_tracer(__name__)
_logger = structlog.get_logger()


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Constants per C-S09-P Rule 6 LAW + D-S09-NN-A LAW signal weights
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Phase ID mapping LOCKED per C-S09-P (mockup banner "4 phases: upload → vision
# → embed → rank"). S-09 uses 0-indexed S-04 canonical (NOT S-07 1-indexed).
_PHASE_IDS = {
    "upload": 0,
    "vision": 1,
    "embed": 2,
    "rank": 3,
}

# Mockup-literal phase labels per Rule 6 LAW + C-S09-P (intent-04-state-A-loading.html
# lines 185-225 designer-locked). BE emits these literally; FE renders trustfully.
_PHASE_LABELS = {
    1: "Đọc nội dung sản phẩm",
    2: "Tìm sản phẩm tương tự",
    3: "Xếp hạng + sinh lý do gợi ý",
}

# Default signal weights per D-S09-NN-A LAW — visual mode (uploaded image).
# FE composeBySignal() helper re-ranks client-side with same SIGNAL_WEIGHTS
# constants when user toggles collab/trending chips.
_SIGNAL_WEIGHTS = {
    "visual":   {"v": 0.5, "c": 0.3, "t": 0.2},
    "collab":   {"v": 0.2, "c": 0.7, "t": 0.1},
    "trending": {"v": 0.2, "c": 0.1, "t": 0.7},
}
_DEFAULT_SIGNAL = "visual"

# LLM timeouts per D-S04-15 LAW Sub-fix 4 calibration:
_VISION_TIMEOUT_S = 15.0   # vision.analyze (mirrors importing_by_images.py:188)
_REASON_TIMEOUT_S = 5.0    # attach_reasons per LLM call (D-S04-15 LAW)
_BLEND_MAX_HITS = 30       # top N from visual_hits to blend
_FINAL_MAX_PRODUCTS = 10   # top N for response per mockup state-0


def _mcp_url() -> str:
    """Resolve MCP service JSON-RPC endpoint from env."""
    return os.getenv("MCP_URL", "http://mcp:5050/rpc")


# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Helpers — reuse from importing_by_images.py per session handoff §6.4
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

def is_vision_blur_error(result: dict[str, Any]) -> bool:
    """3-threshold blur detection per C-S07-J Ω₂ — reused from importing_by_images.py.

    Triggers (ANY fires → blur error):
      1. Overall confidence < 0.3
      2. category in ('unknown', 'unreadable', '')
      3. max(confidence_per_field.values()) < 0.4
    """
    if not isinstance(result, dict):
        return True

    overall = result.get("confidence", 0.0)
    try:
        if float(overall) < 0.3:
            return True
    except (TypeError, ValueError):
        return True

    category = str(result.get("category") or "").strip().lower()
    if category in ("unknown", "unreadable", ""):
        return True

    field_confs = result.get("confidence_per_field") or {}
    if isinstance(field_confs, dict) and field_confs:
        try:
            max_field_conf = max(float(v) for v in field_confs.values())
            if max_field_conf < 0.4:
                return True
        except (TypeError, ValueError):
            return True

    return False


def _current_trace_id() -> str:
    """Get current OTel trace_id as 32-char hex string."""
    span = trace.get_current_span()
    ctx = span.get_span_context()
    if ctx and ctx.is_valid:
        return f"{ctx.trace_id:032x}"
    return ""


def _safe_gather(res: Any, default: Any, rid: str, tool: str) -> Any:
    """Graceful degrade for asyncio.gather return_exceptions=True results.

    Pattern reused from importing_by_images.py:303-309 `_safe()` helper.
    """
    if isinstance(res, Exception):
        _logger.warning(
            "recommend.tool_error",
            request_id=rid,
            tool=tool,
            error=str(res),
        )
        return default
    return res if res is not None else default


# ===========================================================================
# Node 1: vision_analyze — Gemini multimodal + blur check (reuses S-07 pattern)
# ===========================================================================

async def _node_vision_analyze(
    state: IcpState,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
    mcp_client: McpClient,
) -> dict[str, Any] | Command:
    """Call MCP vision.analyze on uploaded image → store _detected.

    On blur/error: emit phase_progress error + error event → terminate graph.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    image_b64 = state.get("image_b64") or state.get("content", "")

    if not image_b64:
        _logger.error("recommend.vision.no_image", request_id=rid)
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "error", {
            "code": "VALIDATION_FAILED",
            "message": "Thiếu dữ liệu ảnh (image_b64)",
            "request_id": rid,
            "trace_id": _current_trace_id(),
        })
        return Command(goto=END)

    # Phase 1 active per C-S09-P + mockup state-A line 200
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["vision"],
        "status": "active",
        "label": _PHASE_LABELS[1],
        "meta": "Gemini Vision",
    })

    try:
        result = await mcp_client.call(
            "vision.analyze",
            {"image_b64": image_b64, "timeout_s": _VISION_TIMEOUT_S},
        )
    except McpError as e:
        _logger.warning("recommend.vision.mcp_error", request_id=rid, error=str(e))
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
            "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["vision"], "status": "error",
        })
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "error", {
            "code": "E_VISION_TIMEOUT",
            "message": "Phân tích ảnh thất bại — vui lòng thử lại",
            "details": {"retriable": True},
            "request_id": rid,
            "trace_id": _current_trace_id(),
        })
        return Command(goto=END)

    # 3-threshold blur check Ω₂ per C-S07-J reuse
    if is_vision_blur_error(result):
        _logger.info(
            "recommend.vision.blur_detected",
            request_id=rid,
            confidence=result.get("confidence"),
            category=result.get("category"),
        )
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
            "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["vision"], "status": "error",
        })
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "error", {
            "code": "E_VISION_BLUR",
            "message": "Ảnh không đủ rõ để gợi ý — vui lòng chụp lại",
            "details": {
                "retriable": True,
                "confidence": float(result.get("confidence", 0.0)),
            },
            "request_id": rid,
            "trace_id": _current_trace_id(),
        })
        return Command(goto=END)

    # Phase 1 done
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["vision"], "status": "done",
    })

    # Surface detected context as `understanding` event (FE PhasesCard payload).
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "understanding", {
        "detected": {
            "category": result.get("category"),
            "attributes": result.get("attributes") or {},
            "ocr_text": result.get("ocr_text", "")[:200],
        },
    })

    _logger.info(
        "recommend.vision.done",
        request_id=rid,
        category=result.get("category"),
        confidence=result.get("confidence"),
    )
    return {"_detected": result}


# ===========================================================================
# Node 2: build_query_desc — template composition for Vespa CLIP embed input
# ===========================================================================

async def _node_build_query_desc(
    state: IcpState,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Build composite query_desc text from vision.analyze result.

    Template per session handoff §5.5 Block 5 Node 2:
        f"{category} {attrs} {ocr_text} brand:... flavor:..."

    This text is fed to vespa.image_nearest_neighbor → server-side CLIP
    embed → 512-d vector → nearestNeighbor against image_embedding.
    """
    detected = state.get("_detected") or {}
    category = detected.get("category", "") or ""
    attributes = detected.get("attributes") or {}
    ocr_text = (detected.get("ocr_text") or "")[:120]

    parts: list[str] = []
    if category and category != "unknown":
        parts.append(category)
    if ocr_text:
        parts.append(ocr_text)
    for key in ("brand", "flavor", "size", "color"):
        val = attributes.get(key)
        if val:
            parts.append(f"{key}:{val}")

    query_desc = " ".join(parts).strip()[:400]
    if not query_desc:
        query_desc = "sản phẩm tiêu dùng"  # fallback if vision returned nothing useful

    _logger.info(
        "recommend.build_query.done",
        request_id=state["request_id"],
        query_desc_len=len(query_desc),
        category=category,
    )
    return {"_query_desc": query_desc}


# ===========================================================================
# Node 3: parallel_fetch — asyncio.gather 3 MCP tools per D-S09-NN-A LAW
# ===========================================================================

async def _node_parallel_fetch(
    state: IcpState,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
    mcp_client: McpClient,
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Parallel fetch 3 data sources:
      1. vespa.image_nearest_neighbor → visual_hits (top 30 + sub-scores)
      2. analytics.co_purchased → collab freq per co-bought category
      3. analytics.product_corpus_size → dynamic N for phase_progress.meta (C-S09-Q)
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    detected = state.get("_detected") or {}
    category = detected.get("category", "") or ""
    query_desc = state.get("_query_desc", "")

    # ─── Step 1: query corpus size FIRST (needed for phase_progress.meta) ───
    # This is intentionally outside gather so meta can be emitted accurately.
    corpus_size_task = mcp_client.call("analytics.product_corpus_size", {})

    # Visual + collab queries fired in parallel with corpus_size.
    visual_task = mcp_client.call(
        "vespa.image_nearest_neighbor",
        {"query_desc": query_desc, "limit": _BLEND_MAX_HITS},
    )
    collab_task = mcp_client.call(
        "analytics.co_purchased",
        {"category": category or "mi_an_lien", "limit": 20},
    )

    results = await asyncio.gather(
        visual_task, collab_task, corpus_size_task,
        return_exceptions=True,
    )
    visual_res, collab_res, corpus_res = results

    visual_data = _safe_gather(
        visual_res, {"items": [], "total": 0}, rid, "vespa.image_nearest_neighbor",
    )
    collab_data = _safe_gather(
        collab_res, {"items": [], "category": category}, rid, "analytics.co_purchased",
    )
    corpus_data = _safe_gather(
        corpus_res, {"count": 50, "cached": False}, rid, "analytics.product_corpus_size",
    )

    # Phase 2 emit with DYNAMIC meta count per C-S09-O + C-S09-P + C-S09-Q
    n_products = int(corpus_data.get("count", 50))
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["embed"],
        "status": "active",
        "label": _PHASE_LABELS[2],
        "meta": f"Đang so khớp với {n_products} sản phẩm shop...",
    })

    # Phase 2 done immediately (Vespa returned synchronously; FE sees progress beat)
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["embed"], "status": "done",
    })

    _logger.info(
        "recommend.parallel_fetch.done",
        request_id=rid,
        visual_hits=len(visual_data.get("items") or []),
        collab_hits=len(collab_data.get("items") or []),
        corpus_size=n_products,
    )

    return {
        "_visual_hits": visual_data.get("items") or [],
        "_co_purchased": collab_data.get("items") or [],
    }


# ===========================================================================
# Node 4: blend_and_rank — Python composite per D-S09-NN-A LAW
# ===========================================================================

async def _node_blend_and_rank(
    state: IcpState,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Compute composite score per visual hit; attach sub_scores + match_type.

    composite = w_v * visual_sim + w_c * collab_norm + w_t * trending_score
    where weights = _SIGNAL_WEIGHTS["visual"] (default BE signal).

    collab_norm: collab_count[product_id] / max_collab_count (normalized 0-1).
    match_type: dominant signal among {visual, collab, trending} per item.
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    visual_hits = state.get("_visual_hits") or []
    co_purchased = state.get("_co_purchased") or []

    # Build collab freq lookup by product_id
    collab_freq_by_id: dict[str, int] = {}
    for item in co_purchased:
        pid = item.get("product_id")
        if pid:
            collab_freq_by_id[pid] = int(item.get("freq", 0))

    max_collab = max(collab_freq_by_id.values()) if collab_freq_by_id else 1
    if max_collab <= 0:
        max_collab = 1

    weights = _SIGNAL_WEIGHTS[_DEFAULT_SIGNAL]
    blended: list[dict[str, Any]] = []

    for hit in visual_hits[:_BLEND_MAX_HITS]:
        pid = hit.get("id") or hit.get("product_id", "")
        sub_visual = float(hit.get("sub_scores", {}).get("visual_sim", 0.0))
        sub_trend = float(hit.get("sub_scores", {}).get("trend_score", 0.0))
        sub_collab_raw = int(collab_freq_by_id.get(pid, 0))
        sub_collab_norm = sub_collab_raw / max_collab if max_collab > 0 else 0.0

        composite = (
            weights["v"] * sub_visual
            + weights["c"] * sub_collab_norm
            + weights["t"] * sub_trend
        )

        # Determine dominant signal (match_type) — which one contributed most?
        contributions = {
            "visual":   weights["v"] * sub_visual,
            "collab":   weights["c"] * sub_collab_norm,
            "trending": weights["t"] * sub_trend,
        }
        match_type = max(contributions, key=lambda k: contributions[k])

        item_out = dict(hit)  # copy to preserve hit shape
        item_out["match_score"] = composite
        item_out["match_type"] = match_type
        item_out["sub_scores"] = {
            "visual_sim": sub_visual,
            "collab_count": sub_collab_raw,
            "trending_score": sub_trend,
        }
        blended.append(item_out)

    # Sort by composite descending; take top 30 (final response truncates to 10)
    blended.sort(key=lambda x: x["match_score"], reverse=True)
    blended_top = blended[:_BLEND_MAX_HITS]

    _logger.info(
        "recommend.blend.done",
        request_id=rid,
        candidates=len(blended_top),
        max_score=blended_top[0]["match_score"] if blended_top else 0.0,
        signal=_DEFAULT_SIGNAL,
    )
    return {"_blended": blended_top}


# ===========================================================================
# Node 5: attach_reasons — parallel LLM + progressive product_ready streaming
# ===========================================================================

async def _gen_reason_for_product(
    product: dict[str, Any], detected_category: str, llm_client: Any
) -> str:
    """Generate Vietnamese reason ≤60 chars per product via Gemini 2.5 Flash.

    Reuse generate_reasons.txt pattern + 5s timeout per D-S04-15 LAW.
    """
    try:
        prompt_template = load_prompt("recommend_attach_reason")
    except Exception:
        # Fallback prompt if recommend_attach_reason.txt missing (defensive)
        prompt_template = (
            "Viết 1 câu tiếng Việt ngắn (≤60 ký tự) giải thích vì sao sản phẩm "
            "{product} phù hợp với yêu cầu ảnh thuộc loại {category}. Chỉ trả về "
            "câu reason, không giải thích thêm."
        )

    rendered = prompt_template.format(
        product=json.dumps({
            "title": product.get("title", ""),
            "category": product.get("category", ""),
            "brand": product.get("brand", ""),
            "price": product.get("price", 0),
        }, ensure_ascii=False),
        category=detected_category,
        match_type=product.get("match_type", "visual"),
    )

    try:
        raw = await llm_client.complete(
            prompt=rendered,
            timeout_s=_REASON_TIMEOUT_S,
        )
        # Strip JSON fences / quotes if model returned structured
        text = str(raw).strip().strip('"').strip("'")
        if text.startswith("{"):
            try:
                obj = json.loads(text)
                text = obj.get("reason") or obj.get("text") or text
            except json.JSONDecodeError:
                pass
        return text[:60] if text else _fallback_reason(product)
    except (LLMTimeout, LLMError) as e:
        _logger.warning(
            "recommend.reason.llm_error",
            product_id=product.get("id"),
            error=str(e),
        )
        return _fallback_reason(product)


def _fallback_reason(product: dict[str, Any]) -> str:
    """Template fallback when LLM unavailable. Vietnamese, ≤60 chars."""
    mt = product.get("match_type", "visual")
    if mt == "collab":
        return "Khách hay mua kèm sản phẩm tương tự"[:60]
    if mt == "trending":
        return "Đang được nhiều người quan tâm gần đây"[:60]
    return "Hình dáng + danh mục khớp với ảnh bạn gửi"[:60]


async def _node_attach_reasons(
    state: IcpState,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
    saver: AsyncRedisSaver,
) -> dict[str, Any]:
    """Generate Vietnamese reasons + emit product_ready per product progressively.

    D-S04-14 LAW progressive streaming: emit each product_ready as soon as its
    reason is ready (asyncio.as_completed pattern).

    Final emit: products event (canonical list) + final event {detected, co_purchase_hint}.
    Strategy β cleanup: await saver.adelete_thread(rid).
    """
    rid = state["request_id"]
    blended = state.get("_blended") or []
    detected = state.get("_detected") or {}
    co_purchased = state.get("_co_purchased") or []
    detected_category = detected.get("category", "") or ""

    # Take top 10 for response per mockup state-0
    top_products = blended[:_FINAL_MAX_PRODUCTS]
    total = len(top_products)

    # Phase 3 active per C-S09-P
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["rank"],
        "status": "active",
        "label": _PHASE_LABELS[3],
    })

    llm_client = get_llm_client()

    # Generate reasons in parallel; emit product_ready as each completes
    async def _process_and_emit(idx: int, product: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:
        reason = await _gen_reason_for_product(product, detected_category, llm_client)
        product_with_reason = dict(product)
        product_with_reason["reason"] = reason

        # D-S04-14 LAW progressive emit
        await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "product_ready", {
            "item": product_with_reason,
            "index": idx,
            "total": total,
        })
        return product_with_reason

    tasks = [
        _process_and_emit(idx, prod)
        for idx, prod in enumerate(top_products)
    ]
    final_products: list[dict[str, Any]] = []
    for coro in asyncio.as_completed(tasks):
        try:
            result = await coro
            final_products.append(result)
        except Exception as e:
            _logger.warning(
                "recommend.product_ready.error", request_id=rid, error=str(e),
            )

    # Re-sort final_products by original blended order (as_completed may shuffle)
    by_id = {p["id"]: p for p in final_products}
    ordered_products = [by_id[p["id"]] for p in top_products if p.get("id") in by_id]

    # Phase 3 done
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "phase_progress", {
        "phase_id": _PHASE_IDS["rank"], "status": "done",
        "success_count": len(ordered_products), "total": total,
    })

    # Build co_purchase_hint payload (top 3 co-bought categories)
    co_purchase_hint: dict[str, Any] | None = None
    if co_purchased:
        target_cats = list({
            item.get("category") for item in co_purchased[:6]
            if item.get("category") and item.get("category") != detected_category
        })[:3]
        if target_cats:
            co_purchase_hint = {
                "source_category": detected_category,
                "target_categories": target_cats,
                "confidence": min(1.0, len(co_purchased) / 20.0),
            }

    # Emit canonical products list
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "products", {
        "items": ordered_products,
        "total": len(ordered_products),
    })

    # Emit final event with detected context + co_purchase_hint
    await publisher.publish_sse(rid, "final", {
        "detected": {
            "category": detected_category,
            "attributes": detected.get("attributes") or {},
            "colors": detected.get("colors") or [],
            "style_tags": detected.get("style_tags") or [],
        },
        "products": ordered_products,
        "co_purchase_hint": co_purchase_hint,
    })

    # Strategy β fast-path cleanup per D-S04-13 LAW
    try:
        await saver.adelete_thread(rid)
    except Exception as e:
        _logger.warning("recommend.saver.cleanup_error", request_id=rid, error=str(e))

    _logger.info(
        "recommend.final.done",
        request_id=rid,
        products_count=len(ordered_products),
        has_co_purchase_hint=co_purchase_hint is not None,
    )
    return {"_terminated": True}


# ===========================================================================
# Graph compile — Pattern A reference compile_searching_by_text_graph
# ===========================================================================

def compile_recommend_by_images_graph(
    saver: AsyncRedisSaver,
    publisher: RedisPublisher,
) -> Any:
    """Compile the 5-node recommend_by_images graph.

    Per D-S04-13 LAW Pattern A + Sx04-7 fix: caller owns saver lifecycle.
    Per D-S09-NN-B LAW: each upload = new graph run + new request_id (FE-side).

    Args:
        saver:      AsyncRedisSaver already entered + asetup() called.
        publisher:  RedisPublisher (lazy-init OK).

    Returns:
        Compiled LangGraph ready for `.astream(initial_state, config)`.
    """
    # Bind mcp_client lazily — one client per compiled graph instance
    mcp_client = McpClient(_mcp_url())

    # Wrap node closures binding publisher + mcp_client + saver where needed
    async def n_vision_analyze(s: IcpState) -> Any:
        return await _node_vision_analyze(s, publisher, mcp_client)

    async def n_build_query_desc(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_build_query_desc(s, publisher)

    async def n_parallel_fetch(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_parallel_fetch(s, publisher, mcp_client)

    async def n_blend_and_rank(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_blend_and_rank(s, publisher)

    async def n_attach_reasons(s: IcpState) -> dict[str, Any]:
        return await _node_attach_reasons(s, publisher, saver)

    g = StateGraph(IcpState)
    g.add_node("vision_analyze", n_vision_analyze)
    g.add_node("build_query_desc", n_build_query_desc)
    g.add_node("parallel_fetch", n_parallel_fetch)
    g.add_node("blend_and_rank", n_blend_and_rank)
    g.add_node("attach_reasons", n_attach_reasons)

    # Edges: linear 5-node sequential per session handoff §5.5 Block 5
    # C-S09-AE Phiên Sx09-C fix: Replace static add_edge with add_conditional_edges
    # after Node 1 vision_analyze. Static edge force-overrides Command(goto=END)
    # returned by Node 1 blur/timeout handlers → graph continues to Node 2-5 with
    # empty state and emits useless phase_progress + final events. Mirror S-07
    # ship pattern (importing_by_images.py:1066-1069) using router function.
    #
    # Router check: Node 1 success path sets state["_detected"] (vision result).
    # Blur/timeout path returns Command(goto=END) which doesn't update state →
    # _detected stays None → router routes to END.
    def _route_after_vision(state: IcpState) -> str:
        return "build_query_desc" if state.get("_detected") else END

    g.add_edge(START, "vision_analyze")
    g.add_conditional_edges("vision_analyze", _route_after_vision, {
        "build_query_desc": "build_query_desc",
        END: END,
    })
    g.add_edge("build_query_desc", "parallel_fetch")
    g.add_edge("parallel_fetch", "blend_and_rank")
    g.add_edge("blend_and_rank", "attach_reasons")
    g.add_edge("attach_reasons", END)

    return g.compile(checkpointer=saver)
